cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.SP

The paper discusses a new sensing framework for image and video processing that combines conventional and compressive sensing. The focus is on image and video enhancement, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed \stone transform is a mathematical tool that enables instant reconstruction of measurements at Nyquist rates, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses real-time compressive video, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SP). Finally, the use of sparsity in compressive methods is related to sparse signal processing (cs.SI).
